\par }{\b\fs24 Commerce
\par 
\par }{\fs24 Cora\rquote Lyst is a HUGE trading centre, linking up most of the island in trade. This in itself generates large amounts of money for the fist treasury. There are however a number of commodities and services which the fists engage in they are:

\par 
\par Fisheries \endash  with the largest fleet of ships, they have many sailors and fishermen working the seas for fresh catch. The seafood is traded in the local markets, and some shipped to Il\rquote Cora\rquote Dvan.
\par 
\par Exotic Herbs \endash  The swamps close to the east and wilds to the west yields a surprising variety of rare plant life. Many herbs sold by apothecary\rquote s in Cora\rquote Lyst can be found no where else on the isle. These are tra
ded of course with the other centres.
\par 
\par Training \endash  The trainers in Cora\rquote Lyst in the art of combat are second to none. Along with the barracks in the military section is a school set up to teach only the art of combat. Although it is expensive it is the best
, and it generate a substantial amount of revenue for fist coffers. It is run by the fists, the various Generals teaching occasional classes on the various aspects of combat, along with hand picked soldiers who excel in their art.
\par 
\par Weapons and Armor \endash  The smiths in Cora\rquote Lyst are excellent when it comes to manufacturing these. But they do rely on the raw materials from Cora\rquote Tyl. Cora\rquote 
Lyst made swords and armor are usually the most reliable equipment in battle.
\par 
\par Engineering \endash  The best engineers live within Cora\rquote Lyst. Many design war machines and some new boats. They also lead the way in the manufacture of traps of varying degrees of complexity.
\par 
\par Other sea related revenue \endash  They are the centre of exploration for other lands on the Island, and this attracts many adventurers. They also build the best boats, and have the best sailors for hire.
\par 
\par Farming \endash  Often Cora\rquote Lyst has surplus\rquote  in this area.
