\par }{\b\fs24 Social Makeup
\par 
\par }{\fs24 The social makeup and status of the citizens of the city are predominately determined by the political structure outlined above. That is the Consul is the ruler etc. There is no recognised nobility in Cora\rquote 
Lyst, standing instead decided by ones rank with the Fists. The higher in the chain you are the likelihood of you bein
g more wealthy and holding more power. This is not always the case, some merchants act independently, paying their taxes to the fists to live within the city, but not holding a direct position with them yet maintaining substantial wealth. 
\par 
